         <listPerson>
            <person xml:id="vol-2-B_M-d2e9177-person" n="vol-2-B_M-Hillel-1">
               <sex cert="high">M</sex>
               <persName type="lemma">הלל</persName>
               <persName type="lemma" xml:lang="en">Hillel</persName><ref type="note" corresp="#d219e4"/>
               <state type="desc">
                  <note>Patriarch<ref type="note" corresp="#d2e9188"/>
                  </note>
               </state>
               <state type="provenance">
                  <note>–</note>
               </state>
               <bibl>Epiphanius,PG41, 412</bibl>
               <state type="addl-Descr">
                  <note>Christian convert?<ref type="note" corresp="#d2e9207"/>
                  </note>
               </state>
               <floruit>272-337<ref type="note" corresp="#d2e9216"/>
               </floruit>
               <note xml:id="d2e9182" n="1"> On this form see vol. 3, under Hillel (2) B/M, p.
                            84.</note>
               <note xml:id="d2e9188" n="2">
                            In this text he is described as being nominated <span xml:lang="gr"></span> (to the
                            patriarchate). On this title see Introduction
                    3.1.3.5.1.</note>
               <note xml:id="d2e9207" n="3"> Epiphanius
                            informs us that on his deathbed he summoned the bishop and <span xml:lang="gr">  
                                </span> (the patriarch was granted
                            baptism and the holy
                    mysteries).</note>
               <note xml:id="d2e9216" n="4"> Was a
                            contemporary of the Emperor Constantine. These are his dates. According
                            to Graetz, he should be dated to 320-65, see Jacobs, Die Institution des jüdischen Patriarchen, 205 and
                            Introduction 7.4.6.</note>
            </person>
         </listPerson>
